
pull the image:

    $ docker pull debian:buster-20201209-slim@0be051a146232e03a67332f2ed33184f0d9efb7e8fbb2d6a091a47f9732e025d
    invalid reference format

    $ docker pull arm32v7/debian:buster-20201209-slim
    buster-20201209-slim: Pulling from arm32v7/debian
    c06905228d4f: Pull complete
    Digest: sha256:0be051a146232e03a67332f2ed33184f0d9efb7e8fbb2d6a091a47f9732e025d
    Status: Downloaded newer image for arm32v7/debian:buster-20201209-slim
    docker.io/arm32v7/debian:buster-20201209-slim


save the image:

    docker save -o buster-img.tar arm32v7/debian:buster-20201209-slim
    mkdir tmp1
    cd tmp1
    tar xf ../buster-img.tar
    mv b11dc122b.../layer.tar ../buster-20201209-slim-layer-armv7debian.tar
    cd ..
    rm -r tmp1


push the tar to a target. use the start script to run.


update 3/30/2021:
  buster images: buster-slim, buster-20210329-slim, 10.9-slim, 10-slim
  use: buster-20210329-slim
  save: buster-img-20210329-slim.tar
  take the layer.tar to: buster-armv7debian-20210329-slim-layer.tar

